title: Serbia Three Month Interbank Rate
description: Serbia Three Month Interbank Rate was at 3.92 percent on Thursday November 10. Interbank Rate in Serbia averaged 6.84 percent from 2008 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 19.18 percent in January of 2009 and a record low of 0.87 percent in February of 2021. The interbank rate is the rate of interest charged on short-term loans made between banks in the local currency. This page provides - Serbia Interbank Rate- actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: National Bank of Serbia
